The user wants me to solve a problem about color diffusion on a grid.
We are given grid dimensions $N \times M$ and a set of initial colored sources.
In each time step, colors spread to adjacent *uncolored* cells simultaneously.
If multiple colors reach the same uncolored cell at the same time step, the cell takes the color with the maximum value.
This continues until no more cells can be colored.
We need to return the final grid state.

The constraints are:
$1 \le N, M \le 10^5$
$1 \le N \cdot M \le 10^5$
